Each action inside an [automation](/api-automation-introduction) now carries its own timing, paving the way for multi-step sequences in a single automation. Previously, timing was a top-level field on the automation; starting with [API version `2026-04-01`](/api-versioning), it lives inside each action as a **step**.

Here's what a multi-step automation looks like in the new format:

```json
{
  "trigger": "subscriber.confirmed",
  "actions": [
    {
      "type": "send_email",
      "metadata": { "email_id": "welcome-email-id" },
      "timing": { "time": "immediate" }
    },
    {
      "type": "send_email",
      "metadata": { "email_id": "followup-email-id" },
      "timing": { "time": "delay", "delay": { "unit": "days", "value": "3" } }
    }
  ]
}
```

If you're on an older API version, the top-level `timing` field still works exactly as before â€” the translation is handled behind the scenes.
